Developing policy and programs to assist commercial enterprises of limited size or capital. Providing advisory services to support the start-up and ongoing operation of small businesses. Encouraging the adoption of innovative practices, processes and products. Includes the establishment of communication networks or resource centres.

Providing financial assistance and services for community-based and non-profit organisations that promote friendship and recreation. Raising awareness of local groups though sponsorship, advertising and facilitating links between organisations.

Developing policy to support the fair treatment of all people, regardless of gender, race, colour, ethnicity, age, marital or parental status, sexual preference, disability or religious belief. Ensuring that government services are implemented with fairness and sensitivity to community needs. Reviewing services and making recommendations to improve access. Promoting equal opportunity and anti-discrimination principles. Includes liaison with target groups to evaluate the effectiveness of equity programs.
Developing policy and programs to enable governments to  consult widely with citizens via social media platforms
Developing research programs to examine Australians' attitudes, beliefs, trends, stratifications and rules.

Managing programs to prevent or repair damage to the ground or earth. Restoring specific areas to their native state or preventing further degradation. Conducting activities to counteract soil erosion or chemical contamination. Includes funding for joint projects with local business or community groups.

Investigating practical applications for geographical data. Providing advice on the development of standards, protocols and specifications for spatial information systems. Includes developing integrated access to information via the Internet, mobile information systems and global positioning systems (GPS).

Administering learning and community support programs for primary and secondary students in target groups. Providing remedial education to assist those in difficulty, and extension programs for the gifted. Includes children with physical or intellectual disabilities, those with English as a second language, migrant or Indigenous children.

Developing policy to support the physical and mental wellbeing of people with particular requirements. Establishing health care programs to assist target groups. Includes advisory and support services for individuals with a particular medical condition.

Developing unique approaches to achieve specific military objectives. Deploying small units of highly trained combat personnel, in response to extraordinary circumstances or where specialist skills and equipment are required. Includes training provided to foreign local forces, when military aid is given to other countries.

Administering the allocation and use of radio spectrum or 'space'. Assessing compliance with government regulations. Processing licence applications for bandwidth and radiofrequency. Monitoring signals allocation to reduce interference and developing long-term spectrum plans with defence, scientific, aircraft and maritime industries.

Developing policy and programs to support the growth of competitive sports and associated industries. Encouraging increased participation and funding for sports and fitness programs. Providing training institutions and facilities for elite athletes.

Overseeing the care and preparation of land set aside for sporting grounds and amenities. Ensuring facilities are kept clean and maintained. Includes field or court markings, turf or pitch quality, spectator seating, and swimming pools.

Providing financial assistance to help build and develop sporting facilities. Identifying groups that may have less access to opportunities in sport. Allocating funds to support the training and development of athletes, coaches, officials and sports administrators.

Developing policy to reduce the supply and use of banned or performance-enhancing substances. Preparing criteria to determine whether a substance is illegal and applying penalties for athletes found in breach of policy. Establishing measures to improve accountability in the prescription of sports drugs. Providing funding for research into doping detection tests. Collaborating with scientists and sporting bodies to share information and research.

Collecting statistics from official providers in Australia and as well as using administrative data to generate statistics. Analysing this collected data to identify trends and other significant information about social or economic activities.
Designing statistical outputs, concepts, methodologies, metadata, and collection instruments .

Supporting and providing standards for numerical facts issued to the Australian community to ensure the information is coherent, comprehensible and consistent. Representing Australia on international standards bodies (such as the System of National Accounts and the International Monetary Fund's Balance of Payments Manual), advising official bodies within Australia about existing statistical standards and consulting on the development of new standards.

Disseminating statistical information for use by a broad cross-section of the community, businesses, the research sector, the media, government departments and agencies, other governments and international agencies. Statistical categories may focus on environmental matters, government activities, population, economic or social matters.

Developing policy to control the buying, selling and trading of shares and securities. Monitoring the activities of stock exchanges and stockbrokers. Issuing licenses, investigating suspected breaches of regulations and applying penalties when appropriate.

Determining a course of action in relation to the deployment of Australia's defence capability. Reaching a conclusion to direct the conduct of military operations. Resolving a dilemma or choosing from a range of options, to realise defence strategic policy.

Assessing military and diplomatic advice. Evaluating circumstances and the relative merits of various recommendations regarding deployment of defence resources or the conduct of military operations. Preparing materials to support decision making to realise defence strategic policy.

Certifying trust funds as superannuation funds, allowing them to accept superannuation contributions and receive concessional tax treatment. Assessing applications against set criteria. Monitoring activities to ensure compliance with superannuation regulations.

Developing policy and programs to encourage recreational visitors to a region. Supporting and regulating the tourism industry. Implementing long-term strategies for tourism development and coordinating across jurisdictions on large-scale projects. Providing funding for promotional campaigns.

Developing policy to regulate the purchase, sale or exchange of commodities. Monitoring the balance of trade, industry protection and subsidy schemes. Includes foreign and domestic activities, and liaison across jurisdictions to support trade agreement negotiations.

Developing policy to regulate road, rail and air transportation systems. Planning and managing schemes for the movement of people or freight. Monitoring the safety of vehicles and their operators. Providing resources for the development of transport infrastructure.

Submitting reports and other official documents to parliament or an assembly for discussion. Tabled documents allow review and scrutiny of government policy and through tabling become public documents. Includes programming documents and other procedures associated with their official tabling.
Setting and collecting taxes or duties on imported goods and resources. Developing policy to control the imposition of charges, and procedures to process tariff payments.

Developing policy to support the collection of taxes and levies from business and the community. Assessing and reviewing the operation of the tax system. Providing taxation advice to individuals and organisations.

Monitoring the documentation submitted by individuals and organisations to ensure it is completed according to taxation laws. Investigating suspected tax avoidance and applying penalties where appropriate. Determining amounts of outstanding tax and implementing recovery procedures. Includes managing payments made by individuals through withholding schemes.

Developing policy to support and regulate industries that transmit signals along a wire or cable to a receiver. Providing advice on the introduction of new technology and the effects of government policy on the telecommunications industry. Includes consultation with peak industry bodies.

Monitoring the activities of suppliers of fixed-line telecommunications services. Ensuring compliance with pricing guidelines, standards of service and maintenance requirements. Managing and maintaining government-owned telecommunications equipment. Setting minimum standards for community access to telephone services.

Supporting industries that transmit content as transient images accompanied by a sound signal. Managing publicly owned television stations and issuing commercial broadcasting licenses. Developing strategies to promote Australian television programming. Providing television broadcasting services locally, nationally and internationally. Negotiating retransmission arrangements.

Administering programs to ensure lawful entrance of foreign nationals intending to visit Australia for a limited time. Processing applications for visas and providing advice to applicants. Includes visitors entering the country for business or cultural purposes.

Managing activities associated with staff separation from the organisation. Issuing warnings and initiating disciplinary proceedings for unacceptable conduct. Arranging exit interviews. Providing access to counselling and advice for retirement or redundancy. Establishing procedures for public sector separations or transfers in accordance with government policy.

Developing policy and administering programs for Australia's self governing and non self-governing territories. Includes providing services in non self-governing territories. Includes policy advice and administration of Commonwealth functions in the national capital.

Administering programs that offer instruction beyond secondary school education, to impart knowledge and develop skills. Developing and implementing entry requirements. Managing tertiary education institutions and facilities. Implementing standards and guidelines to support lecturers. Includes the provision of scholarships and study grants.

Supporting the growth of businesses that provide travel products and other services to visitors. Identifying the potential of new and emerging markets. Providing grants and sponsorship. Encouraging partnerships and coordinating initiatives to optimise tourism employment and create a favourable environment for investment. Includes recognising excellence in the Australian tourism industry through the presentation of awards.

Developing special activities to draw visitors to a region. Marketing and promoting events and attractions as catalysts for tourism growth. Managing publicity to increase awareness of tourism initiatives, exhibitions and trade fairs. Includes the promotion of overseas tourist events.

Establishing a framework of objectives and strategies for controlled urban development. Initiating projects to meet current and future needs for infrastructure and facilities. Providing guidelines to assist applicants for building approval.

Implementing schemes to assist local businesses to compete in regional or international markets and win overseas or interstate contracts. Includes programs to attract investment to Australia, liaison with other governments and industry partners, providing practical assistance such as identifying foreign investment partners and administering grants.

Organising national and international events to promote trade and maximise marketing opportunities. Participating in trade fairs and developing exhibits. Includes activities to raise business profiles in a specific industry, or across a range of sectors.
Administering national trade measurement compliance and enforcement with trade measurement legislation.

Administering programs to ensure that individuals and businesses comply with competition, fair-trading and consumer protection laws. Investigating misleading or deceptive action in commercial transactions. Imposing penalties when appropriate.

Conferring legal ownership over signs or symbols used to distinguish the goods and services associated with a business entity or product. Including processing and approving trademark applications, liaising with trademark owners, granting registrations for trademarks and issuing decisions on disputes over the registration or refusal of  trademark rights.

Administering industry-based training schemes where students learn on-the-job - such as general office traineeships, graduate or cadet programs and service industry training in tourism or hospitality. Monitoring compliance with standards and guidelines.

Managing programs to ensure public transport facilities are readily available to all sectors of the community. Formulating policy to support the provision of transport services to those in need. Developing strategies to assist specific community groups and establishing eligibility criteria for concessions. Includes liaison with areas responsible for public transport construction, to determine short-term and long-term community transport needs.
Developing standards and policies to make public transport accessible to people with disabilities.

Designing systems for the movement of people or goods. Installing facilities to support a network of air, rail and road transport services. Assessing existing infrastructure and planning for future requirements. Includes developing transport corridors, links to airport and rail terminals, and collaborating across jurisdictions on infrastructure development.

Managing public transport networks at a local level. Developing interconnecting services for road, rail and air transport. Maintaining public car parks, bus shelters, train stations, footpaths and cycle ways.

Developing policy to regulate the entry and presence of non-citizens or foreign nationals in Australia. Establishing eligibility criteria, visa classes and entry conditions. Providing on-arrival immigration clearance through the passenger entry control system.

Marketing activities carried out overseas for the promotion of Australia or specific regions as a travel and tourism destination. Organising meetings between members of the Australian tourism industry, travel agents and overseas tour operators. Includes familiarisation tours in Australia for international travel agents, tour operators and members of the travel press.

Implementing the terms and conditions of formal agreements made between Australia and one or more other countries. Monitoring compliance with provisions and obligations .Assessing  the ongoing benefits of treaty participation.

Administering arrangements to uniquely identify motor vehicles. Issuing certificates of ownership and maintaining records to allocate responsibility for individual motor vehicles. Includes processing applications, renewals, transfer, suspension and cancellation of vehicle registrations.

Regulating the design, construction, maintenance and operation of any machine intended for use on public roads. Setting standards for vehicle safety, configuration, noise and emissions. Monitoring conformance through inspections and testing. Issuing or declining certificates of roadworthiness to support the process of vehicle registration.

Managing social support services to returned defence service personnel and their families. Providing advice on rights to financial or other assistance, such as residential care or medical services. Includes funding and support for community-based or volunteer programs providing veterans' services.

Developing policy to support the physical and mental wellbeing of returned defence service personnel and their families. Managing health care programs that address the specific needs of veterans. Establishing eligibility criteria for access to health services.

Administering programs to support commercial grape growing and wine production. Assisting industry growth and development. Encouraging businesses to adopt innovative practices, processes and products. Providing advice on cultivation methods and business management to improve competitiveness.

Developing and promoting programs that offer training and further education for work-related disciplines. Setting standards and guidelines to support the operation of vocational education programs. Initiating joint ventures with industry, schools and tertiary institutions to make use of facilities. Includes the provision of scholarships and study grants.

Providing financial assistance and services for groups and individuals who offer their time and labour to the community free of charge. Raising awareness of volunteer programs groups though sponsorship, advertising and facilitating links between organisations. Includes organising large volunteer groups for major sporting events.

Entering into armed combat with opposing defence forces. Conducting military, naval or air attacks against designated targets. Performing offensive or defensive operations on the battlefield to win campaigns.

Providing services to collect and dispose of garbage. Operating waste management centres, landfill sites, recycling depots and sewerage facilities. Developing and promoting strategies for consumer waste minimisation. Providing services for graffiti removal and street cleaning.

Developing strategies to prevent the loss or waste of water resources. Monitoring dam and reservoir levels, rainfall and projected water usage figures. Recommending water restrictions and other measures to ensure water supplies continue to meet user needs over time. Conducting consultation exercises and education programs to raise community awareness of water conservation issues.

Administering programs to assess the characteristics of water resources, to determine their fitness for purpose. Analysing water samples for the presence of contaminants or minerals to ensure it is potable. Includes testing for salinity, bacteria, pesticides and other pollutants.

Developing policy and administering legislation relating to waterways and water resources. Supporting industry partnerships and cooperative approaches to the management and use of water. Regulating the exploitation of water resources to ensure sustainable quality and availability for household, industrial and agricultural use.

Monitoring water consumption and implementing schemes to regulate water usage. Implementing water conservation recommendations, such as water restrictions. Administering water rights and evaluating compliance with the terms of waterway agreements. Assessing agricultural and industrial water usage practices. Issuing permits for the use of bore water.

Monitoring river flows and catchment areas. Implementing strategies for salinity management and river care programs. Evaluating the effects of land use and climate on waterways. Developing agreements for the equitable use of water resources from river systems that may cross jurisdictional boundaries.

Designing and maintaining online information and services. Managing the supporting software to make electronic publications and transactions available via internal or external networks. Planning the layout of web pages and marking up content.

Conducting research into methods of ascertaining dimensions, extent, size or amounts. Setting and maintaining standards consistent with international conventions for units, values and industrial measurements. Includes testing and calibration of measuring equipment, training and consultancy in measurement science.

Disclosure  of illegal, immoral or illegitimate practices under the control of their employer by government employees (former or current ) to persons or organisations that may be able to effect action such as  watchdog  bodies,  the media or the public.

Administering designated wilderness areas, where the ecology is undisturbed. Monitoring access restrictions. Issuing permits for commercial or recreational activities. Providing advice on developments that might encroach on wilderness areas.

Administering sheltered facilities where animals live in conditions that resemble their natural habitat. Building special amenities, or allocating space from wilderness areas or nature reserves. Supporting protection programs for endangered species and services to rehabilitate injured wildlife. Monitoring the activities of privately run sanctuaries and zoos.

Administering workplace insurance programs. Granting financial compensation for death, injury or disease incurred in the course of employment activities. Providing access to rehabilitation services. Monitoring compliance with government policy on workers compensation schemes. Includes liaison across jurisdictions to promote a consistent benefits structure.

Regulating the conduct of employer and employees across a particular organisation, or between an employer and an individual employee. Certifying agreements with regard to rates of pay and working conditions. Developing policy to support the establishment and use of workplace agreements. Includes enterprise codes of practice.

Administering programs that support workplace diversity in accordance with human resources policy. Ensuring all people have equal access to employment opportunities and conditions, regardless of gender, race, colour, ethnicity, age, marital or parental status, sexual preference, disability or religious belief. Mediating disputes and managing resolution processes. Discouraging offensive behaviour, intimidation or harassment through training and information programs

Administering programs of training that provide learning and development opportunities for personnel already employed in an organisation. Includes courses to improve computer literacy, learn job-specific skills, personal or career development programs and training to maintain or upgrade professional qualifications.

Developing policy to support the maintenance of items or areas registered by UNESCO in accordance with the World Heritage Convention for protection and conservation. Assessing natural, Indigenous and historic sites in Australia for possible inclusion on international heritage lists. Includes liaison with international bodies and community groups to manage the listing process.
